The paper deals with clustering and characterizing Hidden Markov Models (HMMs) based on a hierarchical EM algorithm. This involves tasks such as hierarchical clustering of motion capture sequences, automatic annotation and retrieval of music and online handwriting data. These tasks are related to machine learning, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, computer vision, and signal processing, which are all subcategories of computer science. Therefore, the most likely subcategories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SD (Sound).
